                            jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                            sling:resourceType="menarinimaster/components/text"
                            text="&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;>&lt;span>The Menarini Group continues to increase its investments in Italy and abroad. The Italian pharmaceutical company with headquarters in Florence has recently inaugurated several new buildings at its &lt;strong>Berlin&lt;/strong>-based company, &lt;strong>Berlin Chemie- Menarini&lt;/strong>.&amp;nbsp; The five new structures, some built ex novo and others renovated, represent an investment of &lt;strong>&amp;euro;60 million&lt;/strong> over a total area of &lt;strong>14,000 square meters&lt;/strong>.&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;>&lt;span>The new locations include: a &lt;strong>company canteen&lt;/strong> which can seat up to 250 people and serve 650 meals a day; a &lt;strong>pharmaceutical department dedicated to workers with disabilities&lt;/strong> which houses not only the manufacturing area, but also spaces designed for socializing and recreation for 35 employees and 5 assistants; a &lt;strong>second access&lt;/strong> to the premises which includes a reception desk and shipping and receiving area; a new &lt;strong>Quality Control building&lt;/strong> with 80 employees that will centralize all the company's quality control activities; a &lt;strong>Technical Services building&lt;/strong> that will host the various workshops dedicated to the maintenance and support of the manufacturing processes accommodating 40 people.&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;>&lt;span>&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot; src=&quot;/Portals/31/Images/notizie/cs%20Berlino%2006092016/2016,%20MENARINI%20INVESTE%20IN%20ITALIA%20IN%20RICERCA%20E%20PRODUZIONE,%20IN%20GERMANIA%20AMPLIA%20LA%20SUA%20SEDE%201.jpg&quot; />&lt;br />&#xa;The company canteen at Berlin-Chemie Menarini&lt;br />&#xa;&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;>&lt;span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;span>The investment in Berlin Chemie &amp;ndash; Menarini&amp;rsquo;s new structures began in 2013 and today more than 95% of the project has been completed.&amp;nbsp; It was presented to the German press and to various local authorities including the Mayor of the city of Berlin, &lt;strong>Michael M&amp;uuml;ller&lt;/strong>, who is also Prime Minister of the city-state of Berlin. In Berlin, the Menarini Group has two manufacturing plants and an R &amp;amp; D center specializing in preclinical development and clinical research.&lt;/span>&#xa;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;>&lt;span>Berlin Chemie &amp;ndash; Menarini, located in the German capital, is one of the company's worldwide locations acquired by Menarini in 1992 and represents the Italian pharmaceutical group&amp;rsquo;s continuous expansion in Germany and the most important countries in Central and Eastern Europe and Caucasia. &amp;nbsp;Thanks to these affiliates the Menarini Group is now present in more than 130 countries around the world.&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;>&lt;span>&quot;2016 was a year of major investments for the Menarini Group,&quot; commented Lucia &lt;span style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;>Aleotti&lt;/span>&lt;strong style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong>and Alberto Giovanni Aleotti, respectively President and Vice President of the Menarini Group.&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;>&lt;span>&quot;We are a company with an Italian heart and an increasingly international vision. This is demonstrated by our recent investments in Italy for &lt;strong>VaxYnethic&lt;/strong> and &lt;strong>Lodichem&lt;/strong>, respectively in the fields of vaccines and the manufacturing of pharmaceutical active ingredients, together with our renovation and expansion project of Berlin Chemie - Menarini. &amp;nbsp;One of our objectives since 1992, year in which this previously state-owned company was acquired, has been to work with highly experienced local management of the German market to whom we also conveyed the Italian entrepreneurial vision geared towards internationalization.&quot;&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;>&lt;span>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;>&lt;span>&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot; src=&quot;/Portals/31/Images/notizie/cs%20Berlino%2006092016/2016,%20MENARINI%20INVESTE%20IN%20ITALIA%20IN%20RICERCA%20E%20PRODUZIONE,%20IN%20GERMANIA%20AMPLIA%20LA%20SUA%20SEDE%202.jpg&quot; />&lt;/span>&lt;br />&#xa;Michael Sirotovitch, Rainer Kern, Oliver Igel (Mayor of District Treptow-K&amp;ouml;penick), &lt;br />&#xa;Francesco Nuzzolo, Michael M&amp;uuml;ller (Mayor of Berlin), Reinhard Uppenkamp, &lt;br />&#xa;Christian Matschke, Attilio Sebastio, Piero Batacchi&lt;/p>"
